        <introduction>
            <para>
                Advanced graphics and HiDef effects, like post-processing, require special shaders
                and lookup textures. These assets come pre-built for each platform and can be found
                in this folder:
            </para>
            <list class="nobullet">
                <listItem>
                    <localUri>
                        <![CDATA[<DigitalRise Engine Folder>\Content\]]>
                    </localUri>
                </listItem>
            </list>
        </introduction>


        <section address="Include">
            <title>Add DigitalRise Graphics content</title>
            <content>
                <list class="ordered">
                    <listItem>
                        In the <ui>Solution Explorer</ui> right-click the <localUri>MyGame</localUri> solution.
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Select <ui>Add | Existing Project…</ui>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Browse to
                        <list class="nobullet">
                            <listItem>
                                <localUri>
                                    <![CDATA[<DigitalRise Engine Folder>\Content\XNA\Windows]]>
                                </localUri>
                            </listItem>
                        </list>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Select <localUri>DigitalRise.Graphics (Windows).contentproj</localUri> and click
                        <ui>Open</ui>.
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        In the <ui>Solution Explorer</ui> right-click the <localUri>MyGame</localUri> project.
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Select <ui>Add Content Reference…</ui>
                    </listItem>
                    <listItem>
                        Select DigitalRise.Graphics (Windows).contentproj and click OK.
                    </listItem>
                </list>
                <para>
                    A content project is added to the solution which contains several pre-build assets
                    (effects and lookup textures) in XNB format. The content project does not build
                    anything, it only copies the *.xnb files to the output folder of your project.
                </para>
                <mediaLink>
                    <image xlink:href="Tutorial-01-24"/>
                </mediaLink>
                <para>
                    Let's run the project and check if the post-processing is working:
                </para>
                <mediaLink>
                    <image xlink:href="Tutorial-01-25"/>
                </mediaLink>
            </content>
        </section>


